  "abstract": "Studies on histopathological, anatomical, and biochemical differences between\r\nresistant and susceptible pearl millet genotypes in relation to downy mildew disease were\r\nundertaken at the ICRISAT Ada center, Hyderabad. Indirect sporangial germination by\r\nproducing zoospores was observed. Loaspwe germ tubs penetrated the leaves directly\r\nthrough the epidermal cells, with or without appressarla and very rarely through stomata.\r\n",
